The paper discusses the Artificial Intelligence (AI) capabilities of automated vehicles, their ability to self-drive, sense their surroundings, recognize objects, and perform reasoning and decision-making. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for automated vehicles to cooperate and interact within their socio-cyber-physical environments, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges and issues related to cooperation, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the need for social-AI capabilities for automated vehicles, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) sub-category.
